Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery roette or lotus bowl; interior glazed orange with added red band lined in white; exterior: top of lip glazed, reserved below; inscription cut on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 316)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 669, no. 277)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.859)
